ZCZC GE58
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 242300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL LIES
ACROSS FAEROES AND BAILEY WITH A LOW 1001 JUST W OF
FITZROY. THROUGH THE COURSE OF FRIDAY THE RIDGE IS EXP TO
BUILD SWARDS OVER THE UK WITH THE LOW NEAR FITZROY
REMAINING SLOW-MOV AND STARTING TO SLWY FILL. DURING
SATURDAY THE LOW WILL EDGE EWARDS OVER FITZROY AND
CONTINUE TO FILL WHILE THE RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE
CONTINUES TO EXTEND SWWARDS OVER THE UK. ON SUNDAY THE
LOW OVER FITZROY WILL LOSE ITS IDENTITY WITH A NEW LOW
1002 FORMING OVER THE NEAR CONTINENT THROUGH THE DAY.
THIS WILL CAUSE THE RIDGE TO DECLINE OVER SERN PARTS OF
THE BRITISH ISLES. STRG WINDS POSS FOR TYNE AND FORTH AT
FIRST BUT WILL SOON EASE. OTHERWISE MAINLY LIGHT WINDS
ARE EXP THROUGH TO SUNDAY. DURING SUNDAY STRG WINDS MAY
DEVELOP ACROSS SERN PARTS OF THE N SEA
